.TH MERGE_TABLE 1 "March 2026" "AutoReadme" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
merge_table \- Merge generated file table with existing README.md entries
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B merge_table
\fIREADME.md\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B merge_table
reads a file table from standard input (typically generated by
.BR generate_table (1))
and merges it with the existing file table in the specified README.md file.
.PP
The tool preserves manually written descriptions from README.md while adding any new files discovered by generate_table. Files marked with '!' prefix (older/removed files) are maintained from README.md.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.B README.md
Path to the README.md file containing the existing file table
.SH INPUT
Reads a Markdown table from standard input with the format:
.PP
.nf
| File       | 🧿 | Description                |
|------------|----|----------------------------|
| filename   | 🔩 |                           |
.fi
.SH OUTPUT
Outputs a merged Markdown table to standard output, preserving:
.IP \(bu 2
Existing descriptions from README.md
.IP \(bu 2
Files marked with '!' prefix (older/removed)
.IP \(bu 2
Emoji assignments from input or README.md
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Merge generated table with README.md:
.B generate_table | merge_table README.md
.SH FILES
.TP
.B README.md
The README file containing the "## Files ##" section with the table to merge
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR generate_table (1),
.BR autoreadme (1),
.BR checkreadme (1)
.SH AUTHOR
AutoReadme project